OL,3,C'Spider in hallway': Shocking examples
OL,4,Cof timewasting 999 emergency calls
OL,6,F"When someone's life is in danger, or
OL,7,Fa crime is being committed, seconds
OL,8,Fcount. Unfortunately, too many people
OL,9,Fcall 999 for things that simply aren't
OL,10,Fan emergency or a matter for police,"
OL,11,Fsaid Commander Caroline Haines who
OL,12,Fheads up the Met's Command and Control.
OL,14,F"These calls could mean someone who is
OL,15,Fin genuine need and danger must wait
OL,16,Flonger to get the help they urgently
OL,17,Fneed.
