OL,3,C'Spider in hallway': Shocking examples
OL,4,Cof timewasting 999 emergency calls
OL,6,F"That is why we're running a campaign
OL,7,Fto remind the public of the other ways
OL,8,Fthey can contact us, so we can focus
OL,9,Fon keeping London safe. Let's keep 999
OL,10,Ffree for those who genuinely need it,"
OL,11,Fshe explained.
OL,13,FSome of the main reasons for calling
OL,14,F999 unnecessarily include: asking for
OL,15,Fupdates on previous crime reports,
OL,16,Freporting crimes which aren't
OL,17,Fimmediately happening; reporting items
OL,18,Fstolen days or even weeks later, or
OL,19,Fcivil disputes, such as arguments
OL,20,Fbetween tenants and landlords.
